caption: 30 minutes is too long to wait for an order

I regret ordering food here.  Should have looked at the reviews first.  $21 for 3 pieces of flavorless brisket, cornbread, onion rings, and a can of soda.  Cornbread and onion rings were good but that 12 hour brisket was disappointing.

The sandwich was very worth while and enjoyed every bite as we chilled nearby in one of the lounge chairs. Well recommended if you are perusing through Armature Works or nearby at the Water Works and need a good bite to eat. The service was quick and everything tasted fresh. I highly recommend

Ribs are always at least good and these good. Nice selection of sauce and you can get as much as you want. They were cold and not abundant for the price. I guess if you are at Armature Works and want ribs, may as well, but not worth going out of your way.
Don't got here unless you have 30+ minutes to wait for your food. Yes, it's BBQ but I'm pretty certain they're not smoking the meat per each order.

This menu has several items listed as GF. However when I asked about it I was told they fry their food in the same fryer and there is cross contamination form the onion rings. As I tried to figure out what I could eat I was told “honestly I don’t know about gluten free.” And met with attitude from whom I assume is the lead/boss. It’s unacceptable to work with food, at a place with items listed as GF and know nothing about it. As someone who is celiac their ignorance could’ve made me extremely sick.

The food tastes decent but it is pretty overpriced. I ordered onions rings, which were pretty solid. And I also got the hot honey chicken sandwich. It’s basically just two pieces of toasted white bread with a large chicken tender for $9. I understand that it’s armature works but you can find something better for a better price here.
Burgers are fantastic as are the fries. Honey hot chicken is good. Honey hot sauce ok, Georgia mustard is great, KC sweet is good. Texas hot is a miss. Sides are good
Took 30 minutes to get out food and everything was cold even then. Everything was underwhelming from the cashier to the food the 2.9 rating makes sense now.

Waited 30 minutes for a fried hot honey chicken sandwich. The wait was bad enough, but it comes out and it’s a glorified grilled chicken tender sandwich. No spice, whatsoever. All around disgusting. 0/10. Would not revisit.
Got the honey chicken and got mostly soggy bread and maybe 2 oz of chicken. Worst sandwich ever.

The food was good but I wont be back til well after covid because hardly any of them wore their masks properly and spoke over my food. I told the girl about the masks and she said she'd talk to the girls in the back and when I came back they still didn't have their masks on and they're in THE KITCHEN. Also, homegirl didnt even greet my husband and I, she just looked at us. Over it.
33 minutes to receive my order....a chicken sandwich
BBQ resturant that runs out of BBQ. Didn't not have a single thing in the BBQ section of the menu.
They never have burnt ends which are the only good thing on their menu. They also used to have a butcher counter that they removed so it’s not really butcher n barbecue, it’s just barbecue lol
Wayyyy overpriced..not gonna lie it was good..but not 33$ for burnt ends(very small portion) pp sandwich(small)and beans and corn fritters were burt and very dry...

Horrible food and lazy customer service. My daughter likes the burgers and fries here. We ordered just that. We also order a side of Mac n cheese.  We wait for our food, receive the text that it’s ready. When we pick it up they tell us they are out of ketchup. I told them that they should let people know. When I sat down to eat and attempt the bbq sauce, the fries are cold, the burger was cold, mac n cheese was cold. I go in for napkins, an employee walks over slowly. I ask for napkins and she reluctantly hand them to me as if I bothered her to ask for napkins. At least the can of coke and sprite were right because it wasn’t up to them. Truly a terrible experience and waste of money, not to mention waste of the tip I gave them!
Poor food quality and the taste is not good
BBQ, quality stuff. very delicious. will surely make a return trip. the bill was reasonable. food is like a place in baltimore i liked.

My husband is a huge fan of ribs, wings and all things BBQ, so I knew that BnB (Butcher and Barbeque) would be the first place he would order from. During our first visit they were out of burnt ends and brisket (and it wasn’t even 6pm!). Luckily, on our other visits he has had had better luck! We tried their burnt ends with a side of mac & cheese, brisket and ribs (not all the same day). He liked their burnt ends, but the portion seemed small and we’ve had much better at other BBQ places. The mac & cheese was probably the worst thing we’ve ordered from any of the vendors at Armature Works. Even our younger daughter, who would eat mac & cheese three times a day, didn’t want it. We had much better luck with the last two items. The brisket was served with three very thick slices (see picture below), bread and coleslaw – it had a good taste, but was a little dry. Our favorite item from BnB was their ribs – they were meaty and flavorful, and something we would definitely order again!
My favorite spot for tasty bbq. food was so fresh.

Fries were okay but I ordered a hot honey chicken sandwich and got a lightly roasted grilled cheese with a baked chicken tender wedged in it with some sauce. Also the sandwich was full of really hard bits of something I couldn't find out, my fiancee thinks it may have been bacon but you couldn't even chew it. Didnt finish the sandwich, it was inedible. Do not recommend.

Waited 20 mins for subpar lukewarm food. In fact the order placed after mine received their food first with similar item ordered. The two employees were busy both stocking cans of sprite into their front cooler (while the kitchen put my food near them under a heat lamp for 5 mins). I made the mistake of adding a tip at the beginning— I realize it’s optional but thought food workers need help especially now with income. Had I known the food would have been this bland and poor service I would have not tipped them. The pork sandwich was just ok — the Mac n cheese was weird texture to me with huge noodles caked together. Do yourself a favor and pick out a better establishment such as Empamama’s which have amazing cheeseburger empanadas there.
Great food in a beautiful location

I ordered a bbq chicken blt and got a grilled cheese sandwich. On top of that it took 25 minutes to get a replacement. Even more astonishing, in a time of the covid pandemic... not one employee cooking in the back (which is easily visible) had a mask on.

The bbq nachos are phenomenal. I really can't say as to anything else because I always get the nachos. Everything else that comes out of the kitchen looks great. Definitely recommend this place. BBQ done right.
I finally found the place where I won't second-guess their spare ribs they're so delicious
One of my top locations for bbq. I was so stuffed. The service was very welcoming and observant. It has an awesome feel to it.
BBQ, yeah, so great. Super tasty. The prices are good for what you get. Menu is like a place in San Francisco I liked.
Outstanding spot for quality bbq. the food was amazing. it has a great feel to it.

First time ordering from BNB and honestly wouldn’t go back or recommend. Ordered To-go. Brisket was supposed to come with cole slaw and bbq sauce— only received brisket. Not much smoky flavor and no smoke ring—overdone. Ordered pulled pork sandwich, and again didn’t receive coke slaw or any bbq sauce. Onion rings were a big mush ball and fired in dirty oil. No taste. Potato salad was runny and lacked flavor. Nachos were mediocre at best. No cabbage, tomatoes, & missing other items advertised in description. Not 1 thing was worth the $66.00 we spent. Don’t waste your money.  Plenty of other great BBQ places in Tampa!!
Staff was very friendly food was great

Got the brisket!!!! It was effin awesome, they were almost out we caught the last little bit and they were so generous and nice. We really enjoyed it and the Carolina gold sauce is to die for scoop a beer with it and enjoy the good vibes present from the employees!!! Here’s ur review cheers yalllllll
Food was less than ok. However, the main issue is the food being way overpriced.
Amazing service and food. So happy I ate here.

The best BBQ in Tampa.  I have been to a lot of places in the bay area, but this is a special place.  The brisket is perfect every single time.  The sauces are amazing.  If you don't find something you like here, you're not a fan of BBQ.  Luckily I get to see this place once a month.   Keep up the great work.   Again, go see this place.   It's the Holy Grail of BBQ.
Subpar bbq. Their "side" of coleslaw is one bite out of a ketchup container. This is lowest rated place at Armature Works for a reason.
Love thier burnt ends.  Everything I have tried is absolutely delicious and the staff is great.  Met the manager, Cameron, great guy.  Highly recommend.

My wife and I both agree that this may have been the best burger we’ve ever had. And the Mac n Cheese was incredible. I’d love to try all the other options at Armature, but I’m gonna have a hard time not choosing this place every time.
Had the pulled pork nachos, amazing yum yum
I love there nachos and there breakfast sandwiches!!

They were out of everything but I got the nachos and they were disgusting. They were topped with pulled pork and the pork tasted boiled without any salt. Worst bbq I’ve probably ever had...  French fries weren’t bad.

No seasoning, seriously a bbq place.  I've been here in the past atleast the wings were good.  Just had some yesterday smoked all pretty and tasteless.  I don't know what happened but you may want to undo it before this all comes to an end.

I consider myself to be a huge BBQ fan, but I struggled to eat even half of my single-serving meal here. There's tons of other food options within walking distance, so I'd personally advise you to go elsewhere.
Spare ribs had a good amount of meat & the KC sauce is extra special!

BEWARE! Awful service for mediocre food. My sisters and I ordered our lunch here and I had to wait 25 minutes for nachos and cold, bland premade mac n cheese, people who ordered after me were receiving their food before me! The men at the counter continuously ignored me and served everyone over me!! After noticing how long I had been waiting a worker named Savannah came over to apologize and accomodate me. She is the literal ONLY good thing about this place. I will  never be back nor recommend.

Burger was overdone and dry, fries were soggy and bland, BBQ sauce was thin and weirdly flavored.  Maybe the pulled pork etc. is better, but if you want a burger you'd get better food at McDonald's for 1/3rd the price.

I had the burger and a side of collards. The burger wasn't that bad but not great and certainly not worth what I paid for it. I don't mind paying a premium price but please give me premium food. I understand the space is expensive but don't just charge a lot because your rent is a lot. I also had the collards. They were actually very good. Not bad even though they were very soggy. They had good flavor from the bacon ( bacon makes everything good )I am sure but again the cost for the collards was high. Customer service was fine.

I should preface this by saying that both employees we interacted with were great. The food was not. Ordered a chicken philly and pork nachos. They were smothered in a really thick, salty cheese spread. I mean, it was the star of both items. The pork on the nachos was cold. Not even just kind of warm, it was flat out cold. It was chips, 90lbs of this cheese stuff, some corn niblets and perhaps an 1/8th cup of cold pork. It was weird. We just dig around for dry chips. The philly — idk maybe had chicken in it? We couldn’t taste it. The bread was soggy, it was dripping that onion-y grease and the wet cheese stuff. It’s a tie for which one of us had the most disappointing food. The paper straws didn’t offset the plastic cutlery or plastic cups or plastic wrappers on the cutlery but it did make it impossible to drink our tea which was like tea in that it was brown. They were out of a lot of things by 1230. It was the shortest line out of anywhere in the place so we gave it a whirl. Maybe it was an off day, we just didn’t enjoy our experience.

Horribly bland food with absolutely no flavor. We had ordered the Korean Philly sandwich, mac and cheese as well as the Kicken Wangs. The philly was as if they shoved Hamburger Helper into a bun, very flavorless and gooey. The mac and cheese looked wonderful but tasted as if they didnt even salt the water that the noodles were cooked in. And there was supposed to be cheese on it?!?! Literally tasted just of cooked noodle. The wings were smoked and then fried, the smokeyness was wonderful until you got a mouthful of grease. This was the most disappointing concept at Armature Works.
Best burnt ends ever
Ordered the Korean BBQ and had a long string of hair in my mouth as soon as I bite down! Dry, unseasoned, and bland BBQ. Won't go back, better places with Armature works
Burnt ends and beef brisket are tender and flavorful

We got the burger, brisket, and pulled pork. The burger was average. The brisket and pork were both completely lacking flavor and salt, but were cooked well. The sauces were good. Need to fix the meat-cooking techniques before I would come back!

I grew up eating BBQ. I even appreciate a little fusion or a different twist to a classic favorite.  I'm sorry but this place is terrible.  We were excited because it looked great, but once we sat down and ate it, that's a whole different story.  I know Brisket.....very well.  My daughter ordered a pound to split and the whole thing was fat and oily.  I know. I know Brisket has fat.  Why yes it does and it helps add flavor, but not when the whole thing is fat when maybe a couple slivers of meat.  The chicken was dry.  The collards were soaked in something weird and the mac n cheese while looking divine was rather bland.  I wish 4 Rivers or Mission BBQ had a spot at Armature.  This was the one time in 4 months that we got to go out as a family because of my daughters heart surgery and I feel we should have picked something else.

I had the butcher's choice for lunch. It was the pulled pork on a hoagie bun, fries and a drink for $10. The sandwich was enough for two and it was very good. The bbq sauce was tangy and had a vinegar base. I enjoy it all. My son had the grilled cheese. It was done up right, crispy and cheesy woth lots of butter. He loved the sandwich and fries.
I love the burn ends here. This is one of the few places in Tampa to find them without being loaded up with sugar.

I ordered Korean Philly with Mac & cheese. The sandwich didn’t resemble anything close to Korean BBQ. It just tasted heavily peppered. There were no other discernible flavors. The cheese was listed as being American but it was overpowered by the pepper. The Mac and cheese just tasted like run of the mill white Mac and cheese. No extra flair that I expect from such a cute place.
Pulled pork and french fries are great!

If I could rate like a .03 i would 11.50 for a half lb of the worst brisket ive ever tasted was soggy and had no smoke flavor. The bbq sauce tasted like alcohol. Stay away from this place might be located in a decent atmosphere but the food will let you down sorry just had to be honest about my experience

This place is a contender for not only the worst barbecue in Tampa but also the worst I have ever had. The brisket was mostly fat and Luke warm and the pulled pork tasted like it was smoked with plywood and then covered in oil. Zero stars, disgusting.
I’d try the brisket or burnt tips, but why have it on the menu IF YOU NEVER HAVE IT!!!! 😒 disappointing every time I come half the stuff isn’t even available.... won’t come back
They are extremely slow ribs look good but pulled pork and beef are so fatty and greasy made me sick.Way to expensive and services are really bad.Never going back
The brisket was on point.
Whoever is giving this place 3 stars is an idiot. They have the BEST BBQ brisket, chicken, and pork in town!!! And their collard greens are the best I've ever had!! I highly recommend this place!
Had the burger - great dear and tasty. A little salty with the cheese , but solid choice for a burger. Loved the Bibb lettuce and pickles.
Awful food, disinterested staff, waited over an hour for cold mushy food

Was not impressed. Got the pulled chicken with a side of mac n cheese. The mac and cheese was the only thing I could stomach. The pulled chicken was so dry and chewy and the sauce comes on the side in a little container, disproportionate amount to how much chicken they give you. I wouldn't go back.
Biscuits and gravy were nothing special.  However, my wife and I had their chicken biscuit and brisket biscuit.  Both were incredible.  And you can choose Koolaid to drink!!!!!

This place was the only one that had a line on a Monday lunch hour so we figured we would give it a shot. We ordered two lunch specials which is $10 and it comes with a drink and side of fries. Special for that was "quesadilla burgers" which was just hard taco shells with ground beef. They only had one cook preparing all the orders so that explains the line. Also got the 1/2 pound of brisket for $11 and to be honest, I wasn't all too impressed with the food. The lemonade tasted like a kitchen cleaner and the quesadillas were dry. The fries were delicious though so that deserves one star. The friendly cashier was nice so that's anther star but that's all they're getting from me. Brisket was dry and BBQ sauce tasted like too much alcohol. I think every place in Armature Works is overpriced but it's expected so I can't say much but I can say that I at least tried this place.
Their grassfed burger is the best!
Ordered biscuits and gravy and after waiting 30 mins, they tell me they were out of biscuits and were making them.   Got refund.  Mismanaged establishment.

Ordered: brisket nachos, mac n cheese, and iced sweet tea Overall thoughts: the food did not live up to the hype on this place. Brisket tasted more like minced meat, was not a fan of the cheese on the nachos, and no salsa or sauce was found on the nachos besides cheese sauce. Mac n cheese were nothing extra, just a meh. Wish the food tasted as good as it looked!

Fries were cold, seems like they were. fried in old oil. Meat has no flavor...no salt. Collards were super soggy and taste like sweet pickle. Mac and cheese white cheese powder that comes in the krafts box.  Would not get food here again.

This is the second time I've ate here, both times they have been out of brisket.😕 The barbecue I had was quite delicious, I had the half rib plate and the cucumber salad. This place is located inside of Armature Works Tampa so it's a bit on the pricey side even for BBQ! The half rack rib plate I had was absolutely amazing, next time I'm going to get the full rack. The cucumber salad was very plain, it didn't even look appetizing.

The pulled pork i received was swimming in oil. We dumped it into 1.5 side containers as you can see in the photo. Other than being covered in oil, the pork was flavorless and lukewarm at best. The coleslaw was red cabbage and red cabbage only, no seasoning or flavor whatsoever. The couple beside us had brisket and was also very displeased. They asked if we wanted to take their full plate of brisket home to our dog, I declined.
Horrible service, awful food, overpriced, very disappointed

My wife and I randomly found this place when on a day trip to Tampa.  I am glad we found it!  Anyway, we were both impressed with the hamburger we each ordered.  We were sating to each other that the burgers actually maybe the best we have had.  There was a wait, but it was not an unreasonable amount of time.  I recommend them for sure!
They went over and above to make sure what I ordered did not have gluten or soy. I had a wonderful meal and will happily come back :)  I had the pulled pork with the KC sweet sauce and slaw.

Ordered through door dash. They couldn’t fulfill my order after I placed it because they ran out of brisket. They didn’t adjust my bill. So I ended paying $30 for a chicken biscuit and a bbq sandwich. After waiting an hour for my food (they lost my order). The food portions were a joke. Don’t waste your time eating a Butcher N’ Barbecue.
Good "grass fed" burger and fries.  Reasonable prices.  Little wait but it wasn't that busy either.
Had the Korean Philly cheese steak, very good sandwich with just the right amount of heat.
Long wait, mediocre food, small portions

Terrible service!  Printer did not print my order and I waited until I noticed customers ordering after me received their order.  When I complained they said they could not read the order on the printer. This was their response”Sorry about that”  not let me make this up to you?  They hurriedly gave me luke warm food.
The Food isn't bad the sandwich was yummy but my mac and cheese and French fries were cold which is why I'm giving this place a 3 star
Wings were good. Ribs were dry than a mof.
Just got nachos, looked good but was cold and chips were stale :/
Cold fries, not happy . Past this one up!
The  wait is ridiculous and the food is average.  The prices or ok . 2 pm  wait over nachos and fritters 45 minutes ?
I have been waiting for over a half an our for cold nachos while people who ordered after me have finished their foods

Got the 10$ lunch special, which was a good deal.  BBQ chicken BLT w fries and a drink.  It was tasty though hard to eat.  It was much more a bbq sandwich than a BLT. It came on an undersized overstuffed hamburger bun. The result was very messy though both the bun and the BBQ were good. and there was no L or T. Just meat.  maybe I heard the name wrong?  Anyway this is one of the better stalls at armature works.

Disappointed, nachos you need a magnifying glass to find the brisket. Some of the chips were stale, they cover them with cheese sauce so your hopefull to find some meat, no luck after the search was completed. Corn fritters it's just a ball of batter fried no corn in sight. Go elsewhere for what you pay. The empanadas spot at the other end will not disappoint with Cuban empanada.
Pretty delicious and food is ready faster than you think with the amount of people. Would give 5 stars if the mac and cheese tasted as good as it looks. Mac and cheese is good but not great.

Waited 25 minutes for my lunch, and when I asked about it, the guy at the counter clearly had forgotten about it. The burnt ends were pricey, had two complete blobs of fat, and were drowning in a syrupy bbq sauce. I won’t be back.

Brisket was good. I really like the burnt ends. The pork was over cooked. The chicken and the wings were really good and I enjoyed the Alabama white sauce on the chicken. I would give it 5 stars except for the pork and the prices are kind of high.
The “grass fed burger” tastes exactly like a McDonald’s burger only with fresh vegetables. Still good, but disappointing compared to any other place’s grass fed burger.
Fantastic sweet & spicy burger!! Wow! Highly reccommended.
Awesome brisket sandwich! There had to be almost a pound of meat and I finished every last tasty piece. Looking forward to my next sandwich.
The sandwich was delicious loaded with yummy meat. The young guy who waited on me was so friendly and helpful. I really liked the place a lot.
Underwhelming, tasteless sample sized servings... Drench anything they serve you in Sauce.
Excellent Burnt Ends Sandwich! YUM!
